entry.title: Guatemala Candidates Pledge to Imitate El Salvador's Crime Crackdown
entry.content: Ahead of Sunday’s elections, many Guatemalan voters agree with El Salvador President Nayib Bukele’s hard-line approach.

entry.title: Glenn Youngkin's Effort to Reshape Virginia's Schools Is Off to Modest Start
entry.content: Some of his backers say his gubernatorial clout can only go so far. Other supporters are urging him to further push the limits of the power he has.​

entry.title: What's Happening With Wagner in Russia?
entry.content: Wagner chief Yevgeny Prigozhin pulled back his forces from the brink of a bloody clash with the Russian army in Moscow that threatened to plunge the country into civil war.

entry.title: Wagner's Aborted Mutiny Leaves No Winners in Russia
entry.content: The authority of the Russian state has sustained lasting damage, inviting future challenges to President Vladimir Putin’s regime.

entry.title: What Makes Family? Advocates Debate Importance of Biological Ties
entry.content: Emphasizing genetic ties over chosen family ties could undercut the legal rights of nonbiological parents, advocates for LGBTQ parents say.
